	Top notch Western Hotel in China	We recently spent four nights at this hotel and were impressed by several things. First, the rooms are definitely 5-star and well maintained. Second the complimentary breakfast was the most broad selection of menu choices we'd ever experienced. Both hot and cold menu options, both western and traditional Chinese breakfast fare. Service by concierge and bell staff was excellent. We would highly recommend for a westerner who wants the comforts of home in the midst of China.	
Nov 26 2009 	Superb stay!	Even though we arrived at the hotel long before check in time, we were taken to our room straight away. From the moment we first entered the hotel until our departure nine days later, all of the staff were fantastic. All very courteous. True service with a smile. They made us feel very welcome.Our room was situated on the 11th floor. A very stylish and comfy double room. Sui Yuan restaurant on the 3rd floor is worth a visit, especially for the peking duck with pancakes. It was to die for and at such a good price (8 GBP for a whole duck!). We were with three people and had a lot of duck left, because it was huge.The waitress was very pro active and offered to have two other dishes made of the duck. They were also excellent.Drinks at the bar on the ground floor are nice after a long day of sightseeing (they do a good Singapore sling).I don't fully agree with some of the other reviewers about the location of the hotel being a minus. As Beijing is a massive city, getting around basically takes time from any part in town. It doesn't really matter where you are, in rush hour ( 7-9 am and 5-7 pm) any ride will take long. Other than this, none of the temples and places of interest are in one part of town anyway. So no matter where you are in between the 1st and 2nd ring road, you'll have to travel! I thought this was quite pleasant too. Taxis are cheap and with traveling around the different areas you get to see a lot. Ask the concierge to write down the places you want to visit on a card in Chinese. This definitely saves a lot of heartache as a lot of taxi drivers don't speak English.Xi'dan area is a very trendy area with lots of big shopping malls and bars/restaurants. This area is approx 5 minutes by taxi from the hotel. At night this is a popular hang out for Chinese youngsters. Worth a visit at night.The Park Hyatt is a must for a meal on the 66th floor at China Grill or a drink in the bar on the 65th floor. The food is a real treat and the view is out of this world! All in all we had a superb stay at the Doubletree Hilton Beijing and would absolutely go again.	
