Oct 12 2009 	Everything's good except for the location	I booked this hotel via Expedia during their 2-for-1 promo. This hotel is quite new, probably built just in time for the Olympics last year. All in all, this hotel is grand and beautiful. The exterior and the interior are both very western and modern. Rooms are on the small side, judged by US standards, but very functional. By the way, loved the long sectional sofa/coach/chaise along the floor-to-ceiling window. The amenities are adequate of the Hilton standard. Restaurants serve good breakfast buffet and decent meals. Tip: there is another breakfast buffet location up on the business floors, if you want to escape the hectic crowd in the main hall - but choices of food items are limited at this location. All in all, quite satisfied with the services and the price I paid. One thing - although this hotel is located just outside the 2nd Ring Road on a main avenue, it is actually not close to any major sites or a subway station. Sometimes, taxis are hard to find. And often, you end up sitting in the traffic for a long time to get somewhere.	
