Jun 28 2009 	Terrible location 	We stayed at the Doubletree for 5 nights while visiting Beijing. The hotel turned out to be a disappointment. Its location is not near any of the major Beijing attractions. There are bus stops near by but with the heavy traffic congestion in Beijing, it takes about an hour by car to get to Tiananmen Square, Forbidden City, Temple of Heaven or Olympic Village. Metro is the best bid but metro stop is not near by. You'll have to take a taxi or bus to get to the metro stop. Beijing Taxi is just like in NY City or any other major city, you better have a idea of the distance and cost. The Concierge desk is just too busy trying to get us to go on a package tour every time we ask for directions. We asked for a City map at the concierge but this hotel had no map what so ever. We were given a faded copy of metro map in black &amp; white. We asked for directions to Mutianyu Great Wall and was told that there were only two ways to get there 1. Join a tour for $320 Chinese yuan (about $50 US) per person or 2. Hire a Hotel car for $600 Yuan (about $95 US). I found out from the Information Desk at the Forbidden City to take the dedicated Bus line #6 to Mutianyu Great Wall for $50 yuan (about $8 US) round trip. Another disappointment, our room was not serviced after the first night. We got back to the room at 10 pm to find the room not cleaned or made up. We were just too tire to be bothered. I told the front desk next morning and thereafter was fine but no wash cloth. The swimming pool was not open during our stay.There is restaurant onsite but pricy. You can go to the restaurants across the street for a great meal for 1/3 of the cost. Don't be afraid to mingle with the locals, we found great food and value than the hotel would tell us. The room rate does not include breakfast or internet access. There is additional $120 yuan (about $20 US) for 24 hours internet connection which is very high. Overall, the hotel is new, the room size is same as that of a typical hotel in the US, quiet and comfortable. The location is not desirable, not convenient or near any attractions. The concierge service is poor and hard to get any information. We had great time in Beijing with many thanks from tips provided by locals and City Information Office.	
